<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1458,1860]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,262,1624,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[298,553,1625,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="713 - 721" refId="ref4840" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2003) A synopsis of Morrenia Lindl. (Apocynaceae subfam. Asclepiadoideae). Kew Bulletin 58: 713 - 721." type="journal article" year="2003">Goyder (2003: 716)</bibRefCitation>
suggested 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Meyer" authorityYear="1950" box="[696,877,1625,1653]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[696,877,1625,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">M. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a hybrid between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fontella &amp; Goyder" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Fontella &amp; Goyder" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1237,1381,1625,1653]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="odorata">
<emphasis box="[1237,1381,1625,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">M. odorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Grisebach" authorityYear="1874" box="[151,397,1666,1694]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachystephana">
<emphasis box="[151,397,1666,1694]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">M. brachystephana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the comments made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, T." box="[836,1017,1666,1694]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="49 - 59" refId="ref5936" refString="Meyer, T. (1950) Asclepiaceae argentinensis novae aut criticae, IV. Lilloa 23: 49 - 59." type="journal article" year="1950">Meyer (1950)</bibRefCitation>
. However, he had at the time not seen the type. Having now examined type material at 
<collectionCode box="[844,897,1707,1735]" country="Argentina" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15594" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15594" name="Fundación Miguel Lillo" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" type="Herbarium">LIL</collectionCode>
, we are able to resolve the identity of this plant. There are two sheets with the number 
<emphasis box="[758,936,1749,1777]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Meyer 13845</emphasis>
housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1084,1139,1749,1777]" country="Argentina" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15594" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15594" name="Fundación Miguel Lillo" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" type="Herbarium">LIL</collectionCode>
, one with a flowering specimen, which matches the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fontella &amp; Goyder" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Fontella &amp; Goyder" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[714,857,1791,1819]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="odorata">
<emphasis box="[714,857,1791,1819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">M. odorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and a fruiting specimen, which does not. We have chosen the sheet with the flowering specimen as 
<typeStatus box="[844,961,1832,1860]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">lectotype</typeStatus>
to fix the application of this name.
</paragraph>
